50-| Component                      | Status            | Responsibility                                                                                      |
51-| ------------------------------ | ----------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
52-| `SessionRecorder`              | new (`src/session-recorder.ts`) | Wraps a live `World` (intercepting `submit`/`submitWithResult`), captures inputs/diffs/events/markers/snapshots, emits to a `SessionSink`. Synchronous throughout. |
53:| `SessionReplayer`              | new (`src/session-replayer.ts`) | Loads a bundle (or sink); opens a paused `World` at any tick within the bundle's clean span; runs replay self-check across state, events, and execution streams. |
54-| `SessionBundle`                | new (in `src/session-bundle.ts`) | Versioned strict-JSON archive type; shared by `SessionRecorder.toBundle()` and `scenarioResultToBundle()`. |
55-| `SessionSink` / `SessionSource` | new (in `src/session-sink.ts`) | Synchronous write interface (`Sink`) and read interface (`Source`); `MemorySink` and `FileSink` implement both. |
56-| `Marker`                       | new (in `src/session-bundle.ts`) | `{ tick, kind, text?, refs?, data?, attachments?, provenance }` with closed `kind` enum and `EntityRef`-typed entity refs. |
57:| `RecordedCommand`              | new (in `src/session-bundle.ts`) | Captures a submitted command's `type`, `data`, submission tick, sequence, and result. Replaces `CommandSubmissionResult[]` for replay-relevant purposes (the result-only type still travels for diagnostics). |
58-| `scenarioResultToBundle()`     | new exported function (`src/session-bundle.ts`) | Translates `ScenarioResult` ŌåÆ `SessionBundle` with `sourceKind: 'scenario'` and `assertion` markers. Takes `ScenarioResult` (not `ScenarioCapture`) because the adapter needs `result.name` and `result.checks`. |
59:| `WorldHistoryRecorder.captureCommandPayloads` | new constructor option | Additive, opt-in. When `true`, records full `RecordedCommand` (with payload) into a NEW `WorldHistoryState.recordedCommands?: RecordedCommand[]` field. The existing `WorldHistoryState.commands: CommandSubmissionResult[]` is unchanged (additive, not widening). Required for scenario-derived replayable bundles. Mutually exclusive with `SessionRecorder` per ┬¦7.1 step 2 (only one payload-capturing wrap per world). |
