460-
461-**Range and integrity preconditions:**
462-
463:- For complete bundles (no `metadata.incomplete`): if `tick < bundle.metadata.startTick` or `tick > bundle.metadata.endTick`, throws `BundleRangeError`.
464-- For incomplete bundles (`metadata.incomplete === true`): the upper bound is `metadata.persistedEndTick` (the last successfully persisted snapshot tick), not `metadata.endTick` (which may overstate the prefix that actually made it to disk). `tick > metadata.persistedEndTick` throws `BundleRangeError`.
465:- If `tick === bundle.metadata.startTick`, returns `worldFactory(bundle.initialSnapshot)` directly without replay.
466:- If `tick` falls at or after the first entry in `metadata.failedTicks`, throws `BundleIntegrityError` with `code: 'replay_across_failure'`. Replay across tick failures is out of scope (see ┬¦2; future spec extends `WorldSnapshot` to v6 to lift this).
467-- Engine version and Node version compatibility per ┬¦11.1 clause 9: cross-`b` engine throws `BundleVersionError`; within-`b` warns; cross-Node-major warns but proceeds.
468-
469-**Replay algorithm (clean span case):**
470-
471:1. Find the snapshot to start from. Build a unified candidate set as `[{ tick: bundle.metadata.startTick, snapshot: bundle.initialSnapshot }, ...bundle.snapshots]` (so the initial snapshot is normalized to the same `{tick, snapshot}` shape as periodic snapshots, with `tick = metadata.startTick`). Find the latest entry `S` with `S.tick <= tick`. There is always at least one (the initial entry) given `tick >= metadata.startTick` from the precondition check.
472:2. Construct a fresh paused `World` via `worldFactory(S.snapshot)`.
473-3. For each tick `t` from `S.tick` to `tick - 1` inclusive:
474-   a. Drain every `RecordedCommand` from `bundle.commands` whose `submissionTick === t`, ordered by `sequence` ascending.
475:   b. For each, call `world.submitWithResult(rc.type, rc.data)`. Always replay via `submitWithResult` regardless of which method was originally used ŌĆö `world.submit()` is `world.submitWithResult().accepted` per `src/world.ts:720-722`, so this faithfully reproduces both submission paths.
476-   c. Call `world.step()` (this advances the world from tick `t` to tick `t+1`, processing the queued commands at the start of `t+1` per `processCommands()` semantics).
477-4. After the loop, `world.tick === tick` and the world is paused. Return the world.
478-
479:**Why this off-by-one is correct.** `CommandSubmissionResult.tick` records the *observable* tick at submission time, which equals `gameLoop.tick` *before* `runTick()` advances it. A command observed at `submissionTick === 0` is processed by the step that advances `0 ŌåÆ 1`. The replay loop submits at `t` and immediately steps `t ŌåÆ t+1`, matching this exactly. Replaying a bundle with `startTick === 0` and `targetTick === 5` runs five iterations (`t = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4`), each submitting that tick's commands then stepping; the resulting world is at `tick === 5`, which is the requested target.
480-
481:**Submission ordering within a tick.** Multiple commands at the same `submissionTick` are replayed in `sequence` ascending, matching the recorder's capture order, matching the original engine queue order. Mid-tick submissions (which violate ┬¦11.1) are out of scope for replay; if a system calls `world.submit()` during `step()`, both the recorded submission and the replayed system's re-submission will fire ŌĆö `selfCheck()` will surface this as a command-stream divergence.
482-
483-The returned `World` is fully functional ŌĆö caller can step further, inspect state, query events. This is the agent's primary debugging affordance.
484-
485-### 9.2 Replay determinism guarantee
486-
487:`openAt(tick)` is deterministic given the same `worldFactory`, the same engine major version, and the same Node major version (per H5 in iter-1 review). If the bundle's recorded snapshot at `tick` exists, replay produces a snapshot equal to it at every JSON path AND a per-tick event stream and execution stream identical to the recording's. Divergence in any of the three streams indicates a determinism contract violation per ┬¦11, or (rarely) a transcendental-Math difference across V8 majors.
488-
489:The replayer does not silently mask divergence; `selfCheck()` is the explicit verification path.
490-
491-### 9.3 `selfCheck()` algorithm
492-
493-```
494-// Build snapshot list normalized as { tick, snapshot } including the initial snapshot
495:allSnapshots = [{ tick: metadata.startTick, snapshot: initialSnapshot }, ...bundle.snapshots]
496-// segments are consecutive pairs
497-segments = pairs(allSnapshots)
498:// segments has at least one entry because the recorder writes a terminal snapshot on disconnect()
499-// by default (see ┬¦7.1 step 6 / `terminalSnapshot` config option). A bundle with terminalSnapshot: false
500-// AND no periodic snapshots produces segments = [] and selfCheck() returns
501-// { ok: true, checkedSegments: 0 } with a console warning ŌĆö diagnostic-only mode.
502-
503-For each (snapshotA, snapshotB) in segments:
504:  worldA = worldFactory(snapshotA.snapshot)
505-
506:  // Subscribe to onCommandExecution to accumulate replay-side execution results
507:  replayExecutions = []
508:  worldA.onCommandExecution(r => replayExecutions.push(r))
509-
510-  for each tick t from snapshotA.tick to snapshotB.tick - 1:
511-    drain RecordedCommands at submissionTick === t (ordered by sequence)
512-    submitWithResult each via worldA
513-    worldA.step()
514-    if checkEvents: compare worldA.getEvents() to bundle's tick entry events at t+1
515:    if checkExecutions: compare replayExecutions filtered to tick === t+1 to
516-                        bundle.executions filtered to tick === t+1
517-
518-  if checkState: actualB = worldA.serialize(); compare to snapshotB.snapshot via fast deep-equal
--
523-Notes:
524-
525-- **Initial-to-first-snapshot segment is included.** Normalizing the initial snapshot into the unified snapshot list is critical: a determinism bug in the first 1000 ticks (before the first periodic snapshot) would otherwise go undetected.
526:- **Terminal snapshot guarantees coverage of short sessions.** Per ┬¦7.1 step 6, `disconnect()` writes a terminal snapshot by default. A 500-tick session with default `snapshotInterval: 1000` thus has `allSnapshots = [initial, terminal]`, producing one segment that selfCheck verifies. Without this, the ┬¦13.5 CI gate would silently pass on every short scenario.
527-- **Scenario bundles converge.** Scenario bundles produce `bundle.snapshots: [{ tick: result.tick, snapshot: result.snapshot }]` ŌĆö one entry ŌĆö plus the initial snapshot, so `segments = [(initial, final)]`. selfCheck verifies the full scenario span.
528:- **Execution stream comparison via listener.** The replay world's `onCommandExecution` listener accumulates results during each segment's replay; the bundle's `executions` array is filtered to the same tick range and compared. There is no `world.getCommandExecutionResults()` getter ŌĆö the listener is the only path.
529-- **State equality** uses a fast recursive deep-equal that short-circuits on first mismatch and produces a best-effort dotted `firstDifferingPath` (`"components.position[42].x"`). Snapshot key ordering is stable per the snapshot serialization invariant (Map insertion order); two equal snapshots have equal key order, so deep-equal need not canonicalize.
530-- **Event/execution equality** is by ordered structural equality on the per-tick array. Order matters.
531:- **Cost.** selfCheck replays the full timeline once. For a 10000-tick bundle with 10 snapshots + initial + terminal = 11 segments, that's roughly 11 ├Ś ~900 = ~10000 ticks of replay plus deserialize/factory cost per segment. Cost benchmarks live in ┬¦13.2.
