684-- **Clause 1: external-only mutation.** Clean: command-driven mutation only. Violation: a setup callback calls `world.setComponent` between ticks during a recording. Expect state divergence.
685:- **Clause 2: no mid-tick submit.** Clean: systems do not submit. Violation: a system calls `world.submit()`. Expect command-stream / execution divergence on replay.
686-- **Clause 3: routed randomness.** Clean: systems use `world.random()`. Violation: a system uses `Math.random()`. Expect state divergence.
687-- **Clause 4: pure validators.** Clean: validators are pure. Violation: a validator calls `world.setComponent` (mutation side effect). Expect state divergence.
688-- **Clause 5: no wall-clock.** Clean: systems use `world.tick`. Violation: a system uses `Date.now()`. Expect state divergence.
