docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-471-1. Find the snapshot to start from. Build a unified candidate set as `[{ tick: bundle.metadata.startTick, snapshot: bundle.initialSnapshot }, ...bundle.snapshots]` (so the initial snapshot is normalized to the same `{tick, snapshot}` shape as periodic snapshots, with `tick = metadata.startTick`). Find the latest entry `S` with `S.tick <= tick`. There is always at least one (the initial entry) given `tick >= metadata.startTick` from the precondition check.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-472-2. Construct a fresh paused `World` via `worldFactory(S.snapshot)`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-473-3. For each tick `t` from `S.tick` to `tick - 1` inclusive:
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:474:   a. Drain every `RecordedCommand` from `bundle.commands` whose `submissionTick === t`, ordered by `sequence` ascending.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-475-   b. For each, call `world.submitWithResult(rc.type, rc.data)`. Always replay via `submitWithResult` regardless of which method was originally used ŌĆö `world.submit()` is `world.submitWithResult().accepted` per `src/world.ts:720-722`, so this faithfully reproduces both submission paths.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-476-   c. Call `world.step()` (this advances the world from tick `t` to tick `t+1`, processing the queued commands at the start of `t+1` per `processCommands()` semantics).
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-477-4. After the loop, `world.tick === tick` and the world is paused. Return the world.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-478-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:479:**Why this off-by-one is correct.** `CommandSubmissionResult.tick` records the *observable* tick at submission time, which equals `gameLoop.tick` *before* `runTick()` advances it. A command observed at `submissionTick === 0` is processed by the step that advances `0 ŌåÆ 1`. The replay loop submits at `t` and immediately steps `t ŌåÆ t+1`, matching this exactly. Replaying a bundle with `startTick === 0` and `targetTick === 5` runs five iterations (`t = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4`), each submitting that tick's commands then stepping; the resulting world is at `tick === 5`, which is the requested target.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-480-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:481:**Submission ordering within a tick.** Multiple commands at the same `submissionTick` are replayed in `sequence` ascending, matching the recorder's capture order, matching the original engine queue order. Mid-tick submissions (which violate ┬¦11.1) are out of scope for replay; if a system calls `world.submit()` during `step()`, both the recorded submission and the replayed system's re-submission will fire ŌĆö `selfCheck()` will surface this as a command-stream divergence.
