docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-523-Notes:
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-524-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-525-- **Initial-to-first-snapshot segment is included.** Normalizing the initial snapshot into the unified snapshot list is critical: a determinism bug in the first 1000 ticks (before the first periodic snapshot) would otherwise go undetected.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:526:- **Terminal snapshot guarantees coverage of short sessions.** Per ┬¦7.1 step 6, `disconnect()` writes a terminal snapshot by default. A 500-tick session with default `snapshotInterval: 1000` thus has `allSnapshots = [initial, terminal]`, producing one segment that selfCheck verifies. Without this, the ┬¦13.5 CI gate would silently pass on every short scenario.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:527:- **Scenario bundles converge.** Scenario bundles produce `bundle.snapshots: [{ tick: result.tick, snapshot: result.snapshot }]` ŌĆö one entry ŌĆö plus the initial snapshot, so `segments = [(initial, final)]`. selfCheck verifies the full scenario span.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-528-- **Execution stream comparison via listener.** The replay world's `onCommandExecution` listener accumulates results during each segment's replay; the bundle's `executions` array is filtered to the same tick range and compared. There is no `world.getCommandExecutionResults()` getter ŌĆö the listener is the only path.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-529-- **State equality** uses a fast recursive deep-equal that short-circuits on first mismatch and produces a best-effort dotted `firstDifferingPath` (`"components.position[42].x"`). Snapshot key ordering is stable per the snapshot serialization invariant (Map insertion order); two equal snapshots have equal key order, so deep-equal need not canonicalize.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-530-- **Event/execution equality** is by ordered structural equality on the per-tick array. Order matters.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-531-- **Cost.** selfCheck replays the full timeline once. For a 10000-tick bundle with 10 snapshots + initial + terminal = 11 segments, that's roughly 11 ├Ś ~900 = ~10000 ticks of replay plus deserialize/factory cost per segment. Cost benchmarks live in ┬¦13.2.
--
