docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-548-- `metadata.sourceKind = 'scenario'`, `metadata.sourceLabel = options?.sourceLabel ?? result.name`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-549-- `metadata.engineVersion` ŌåÉ `package.json` version at translate time. `metadata.nodeVersion` ŌåÉ `options?.nodeVersion ?? process.version`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-550-- `metadata.startTick` ŌåÉ `result.history.initialSnapshot.tick`. **Not hardcoded to 0.** `runScenario` may be invoked on a world that has already advanced beyond tick 0 (e.g., from a deserialized snapshot, or from setup-time `world.step()` calls). `result.history.initialSnapshot.tick` is the authoritative starting point ŌĆö `runScenario` calls `history.clear()` after `setup` runs (`src/scenario-runner.ts:175`) which rebases `initialSnapshot` to the post-setup, pre-run state. **Precondition:** `result.history.initialSnapshot !== null`. If null (which happens when the scenario's `WorldHistoryRecorder` was configured with `captureInitialSnapshot: false` ŌĆö still allowed on the legacy recorder), `scenarioResultToBundle()` throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_initial_snapshot')`. Replayable scenario bundles require BOTH `captureInitialSnapshot: true` (the default) AND `captureCommandPayloads: true` on the scenario's history config ŌĆö see ┬¦10.2.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:551:- `metadata.endTick` ŌåÉ `result.tick` (final tick when checks ran).
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-552-- `metadata.durationTicks` ŌåÉ `metadata.endTick - metadata.startTick`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-553-- `initialSnapshot` ŌåÉ `result.history.initialSnapshot`. **Note:** post-setup, not pre-setup. Replaying a scenario-derived bundle reproduces the run from the post-setup state forward; consumers that want to replay from raw `World` construction must reproduce `setup()` in their `worldFactory` before deserializing the snapshot. Document in ┬¦14's scenario-runner guide section.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-554-- `ticks` ŌåÉ `result.history.ticks`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-555-- `commands` ŌåÉ `result.history.recordedCommands ?? []` (a new optional field on `WorldHistoryState` populated only when the scenario's `WorldHistoryRecorder` was constructed with `captureCommandPayloads: true`; see ┬¦10.2). When this field is absent or empty, the resulting bundle is diagnostic-only (`openAt` throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_replay_payloads')`). The legacy `result.history.commands: CommandSubmissionResult[]` field is unchanged for backward compatibility ŌĆö it travels in the bundle's `commands` field too only if a future schema decides to denormalize; for v1 the bundle uses just `recordedCommands`-derived data.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-556-- `executions` ŌåÉ `result.history.executions`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-557-- `failures` ŌåÉ `result.history.failures`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:558:- `snapshots` ŌåÉ `[{ tick: result.tick, snapshot: result.snapshot }]`. Single entry; selfCheck will check the segment from `initialSnapshot` to this final snapshot. Future enhancement could add periodic snapshots via a scenario option.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-559-- `markers` ŌåÉ one assertion marker per `result.checks` outcome:
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-560-  ```
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:561:  { id, tick: result.tick, kind: 'assertion', provenance: 'engine',
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-562-    text: outcome.name, data: { passed: outcome.passed, failure: outcome.failure } }
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-563-  ```
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:564:  `ScenarioCheckOutcome` does NOT currently track per-check tick (verified at `src/scenario-runner.ts:44-48`). All assertion markers share `tick === result.tick`. A future spec extends `ScenarioCheckOutcome` to track per-check tick, after which the adapter can place each marker at its actual check tick.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-565-- `attachments` ŌåÉ empty array; scenarios have no attachment producer.
