docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-567-### 10.2 `captureCommandPayloads` on `WorldHistoryRecorder`
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-568-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-569-For scenarios to produce replayable bundles, `WorldHistoryRecorder` must capture full `RecordedCommand` payloads (not just `CommandSubmissionResult` results). This spec **commits to adding a `captureCommandPayloads: boolean` option to `WorldHistoryRecorder`'s constructor** (defaulting to `false` to preserve the existing rolling-buffer-debug use case). When `true`:
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-570-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:571:- The recorder wraps `submitWithResult` (matching `SessionRecorder`'s pattern; `submit` delegates through it) to capture `{ type, data, sequence, submissionTick, result }` into a NEW field on `WorldHistoryState`: `recordedCommands?: RecordedCommand[]`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-572-- The existing `WorldHistoryState.commands: CommandSubmissionResult[]` field is unchanged. Public-type contract is preserved ŌĆö adding a new optional field is purely additive (per `AGENTS.md` `c`-bump policy).
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-573-- Per ┬¦7.1 step 2, `WorldHistoryRecorder({ captureCommandPayloads: true })` and `SessionRecorder` are mutually exclusive on a given world (only one payload-capturing wrap may exist; second `connect()` throws `RecorderClosedError(code: 'recorder_already_attached')`). Default-config `WorldHistoryRecorder` instances (no payload capture) compose freely with `SessionRecorder`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-574-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-575-This is an additive, opt-in change to `WorldHistoryRecorder`. The default behavior (capacity 64, payload-less command capture, no wrap) is preserved for existing consumers. Scenarios that want replayable bundles opt in:
