docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-666-- **`SessionBundle` schema**: strict-JSON round-trip via `JSON.stringify` + `JSON.parse`; rejection of malformed bundles by `assertJsonCompatible`; sidecar attachment refs are present in JSON but bytes are NOT.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-667-- **`MemorySink` / `MemorySource`**: in-memory accumulation, `toBundle()` correctness, sync method semantics, `readSidecar` for sidecar-mode attachments, sidecar opt-in flag.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-668-- **`FileSink` / `FileSource`**: full file layout (manifest + 5 jsonl streams + snapshots/ + attachments/); manifest rewrites at open / per-snapshot / close per ┬¦5.2; atomic-rename invariant; JSONL append-only invariant; attachment policy (FileSink defaults to sidecar; explicit `{ sidecar: false }` opts into dataUrl embedding for small blobs only); recovery from `incomplete: true` bundles (read prefix up to `metadata.persistedEndTick`); tolerance of partial JSONL line on read.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-669-- **`Marker`**: kind enum exhaustiveness; `EntityRef` validation (id+generation matching); cells; tickRange; opaque `data` round-trip; provenance discrimination.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:670:- **`scenarioResultToBundle()`**: assertion markers produced one per `result.checks` outcome with `provenance: 'engine'`; `metadata.sourceKind`/`sourceLabel`/`startTick` (from `result.history.initialSnapshot.tick`)/`endTick` (from `result.tick`) populated correctly; bundle without command payloads warns and `selfCheck()` returns `checkedSegments: 0`; bundle WITH payloads (scenario opted into `captureCommandPayloads: true`) is replayable.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-671-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-672-### 13.2 Integration tests
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-673-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:674:- **Record ŌåÆ replay ŌåÆ state-equal.** Build a small scenario (10 entities, 1000 ticks, varied commands including accepted+rejected, multiple validators), record with `snapshotInterval: 100`, serialize the bundle, deserialize via `SessionReplayer.fromBundle`, call `openAt(N)` for representative ticks (initial, mid-segment, snapshot boundary, last tick), assert `world.serialize()` deep-equals the corresponding recorded snapshot.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-675-- **MemorySink Ōåö FileSink parity.** Record the same scenario via both sinks; assert the resulting bundles are structurally equal modulo `attachments[].ref` (dataUrl vs sidecar). Replay both; assert identical openAt results.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-676-- **Scenario integration.** Convert an existing scenario test (e.g. one of the existing `runScenario(...)` tests) to also assert `scenarioResultToBundle(result)` produces a valid bundle with one `kind: 'assertion'` marker per `result.checks` outcome, matching `outcome.passed` and `outcome.failure`.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-677-- **Long capture smoke.** 10000-tick session with 50 commands per tick, default snapshot cadence (10 snapshots), `MemorySink`. Assert bundle loads, `selfCheck()` passes, `openAt` for any tick completes within reasonable time. Throughput target: `openAt()` walking a single segment runs Ōēź 5x recording throughput; `selfCheck()` over N segments scales linearly. Drop the conflated multiplier.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-678-- **Cross-snapshot replay.** `openAt(tick)` where `tick` falls between two snapshots ŌĆö verify the replayer correctly walks from the prior snapshot through recorded commands.
--
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-694-Plus:
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-695-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-696-- **Determinism upheld** baseline: a clean scenario; `selfCheck()` reports `ok: true` with empty divergence arrays.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-697-- **`stopOnFirstDivergence`**: with deliberate violations at multiple snapshot pairs and the option set, assert only the first is reported.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:698:- **selfCheck includes initial-to-first-snapshot segment.** Recording where a determinism violation occurs in the first 100 ticks (before the first periodic snapshot at `snapshotInterval: 1000`) ŌĆö selfCheck must surface it because the segment `(initialSnapshot, snapshots[0])` is checked.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-699-- **selfCheck on scenario bundles.** A scenario bundle has `snapshots: [final]` only; selfCheck checks `(initialSnapshot, final)` ŌĆö exactly one segment.
