docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-831-The following are intentionally left for the writing-plans phase or for future specs. They are not blocking spec acceptance.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-832-
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-833-1. **Snapshot equality algorithm.** ┬¦9.3 commits to recursive walk + short-circuit (the alternative ŌĆö canonical-JSON hash ŌĆö loses `firstDifferingPath`). Snapshot key ordering is stable per the snapshot serialization invariant (Map insertion order), so deep-equal need not canonicalize. Benchmark on the long-capture smoke test will validate throughput target.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-834-2. **Versioning policy for breaking bundle changes.** When `schemaVersion` bumps to 2, do we ship a migrator (`migrate(bundle, fromVersion, toVersion)`) or simply reject older versions? Decision deferred to the first time a bump is needed.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:835:3. **Default `snapshotInterval` of 1000.** Validated by the long-capture smoke test in ┬¦13.2. May be tuned based on representative bundle sizes.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-836-4. **`ReplayerConfig.worldFactory` ergonomics.** Per ADR 4, the factory is part of the determinism contract. A future spec may add a registration-manifest shape-check to surface factory drift with a clearer diagnostic; not v1.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-837-5. **Bundle command/execution/marker stream sharding.** A 10000-tick ├Ś 50-command-per-tick session produces 500K command entries; `commands.jsonl` would be hundreds of MB. v1 ships single-file streams; future enhancement may rotate at a configurable size threshold (e.g. `commands.0001.jsonl`, `commands.0002.jsonl`). Manifest already references streams by filename, so adding rotation is non-breaking.
docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md-838-6. **`BufferedSink` proxy.** A future enhancement that wraps any `SessionSink` and batches writes asynchronously to mitigate tick-rate impact for production captures. Not v1 because it requires either an explicit drain policy (write-on-tick-boundary, write-on-marker, max-buffer-size) or a complete async-aware listener restructure. Worth specifying when synthetic playtest needs it.
